BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:UC Love Data Week 2026 (February 9-13)
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260209T190000Z
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260210T000000Z
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51959615320335
DESCRIPTION:UC Love Data Week (UCLDW) is a week-long offering of presentat
 ions and workshops from across the University of California focused on all
  things data. All members of the UC community are welcome to attend this f
 ree\, virtual event. See the full schedule by day and register now. With o
 ver 20 presentations and workshops\, whether you’re working with qualita
 tive or quantitative data\, there’s plenty to choose from. This year's t
 opics include: Data visualizationIntegrating AIWorking with data in R and 
 PythonData repositoriesand much more! Workshops taught during UCLDW by UC 
 Davis DataLab and Librarians include: Monday\, 2/9 at 11 AM - Intro to Ope
 nRefine for Data CleaningMonday\, 2/9 at 2 PM - How to Use Data Repository
  FindersWednesday\, 2/11 at 10 AM - How I Slacked at Work and Accidentally
  Built an Automated\, AI Driven ETL PipelineThursday\, 2/12 at 10 AM - Vis
 ualizing data with ggplot for R users (offered in person at DataLab and vi
 a Zoom!) For more information please visit the UC Love Data Week website. 
 Please register with your UC campus email. Zoom links will be emailed to r
 egistered participants.
URL:https://events.library.ucdavis.edu/event/uc-love-data-week-2026-februa
 ry-9-13
X-SOURCE:UC Davis Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Workshop: Intro to OpenRefine for Data Cleaning
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260209T190000Z
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260209T200000Z
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51836881356432
DESCRIPTION:Learn how to clean\, standardize\, and transform messy data us
 ing OpenRefine\, a powerful open source tool for working with large or inc
 onsistent datasets. This hands on session will introduce key features such
  as faceting\, clustering\, data transformation\, and enrichment. OpenRefi
 ne runs locally in your web browser and works especially well with CSV and
  TSV files. What You’ll Learn • How to explore and assess a dataset 
 • Techniques for identifying and resolving inconsistencies • Ways to s
 plit\, transform\, and standardize data Prerequisites • Install OpenRefi
 ne before the workshop by going to https://openrefine.org/ • Basic famil
 iarity with Excel or Google Sheets Who Should Attend Researchers\, student
 s\, librarians\, and anyone who works with structured data and wants faste
 r\, more reliable cleanup workflows. This workshop is offered as part of U
 C Love Data Week. Advance registration required. Questions? Contact datala
 b-training@ucdavis.edu.
URL:https://events.library.ucdavis.edu/event/workshop-w2026-open-refine
X-SOURCE:UC Davis Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Collaborative Data Science Office Hours (virtual)
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260209T210000Z
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260209T220000Z
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_50756015390844
DESCRIPTION:DataLab and colleagues from research computing and statistical
  service units across UC Davis offer weekly free virtual office hours duri
 ng which UC Davis researchers can obtain help and advice on working with t
 heir data. During these short\, just-in-time sessions we meet with faculty
 \, students\, postdoctoral scholars\, and research staff from all domains 
 across the University to discuss their research challenges. Register in ad
 vance for the Zoom link. This helps us connect you to the right expert for
  your question. In addition to DataLab\, the collaborative data science of
 fice hours are supported by: Biostatistics (Clinical and Translational Sci
 ence Center\, CTSC)Computational Research Data Service (College of Letters
  & Science)High Performance Computing (HPC) CoreResearcher Services (UC Da
 vis Library)Stat Lab (Department of Statistics)Common office hours help to
 pics include: Open Source Programming (R\, Python\, Julia\, etc.)Reproduci
 ble research computing and data scienceResponsible and ethical data scienc
 eData gathering\, organization\, databases\, and experimental designData a
 nalysis\, statistics\, and explorationData visualizationMachine learning a
 nd neural networksText mining and natural language processingGeospatial sc
 iencesRemote and high performance computingComputational pedagogy… and m
 ore!Please note that drop-in office hours are not offered during Universit
 y holidays\, academic breaks and finals week. Summer schedule varies based
  on availability. Note: Office hours are intended for short "just in time"
  research support. If you require extensive assistance we may refer you a 
 recharge service\, upcoming funding/project calls\, and/or other resources
 . We are unable to provide support for assigned coursework (homework assig
 nments\, class projects\, etc.) during office hours. If you need such help
  please contact your instructor or TA for assistance. If you need help wit
 h technical problems such system administration and hardware issues\, chec
 k out the the UC Davis ServiceHub and/or contact your departmental IT.
URL:https://events.library.ucdavis.edu/event/copy-of-collaborative-data-sc
 ience-office-hours-virtual
X-SOURCE:UC Davis Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Workshop: How to Use Data Repository Finders
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260209T220000Z
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260209T230000Z
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51836922377962
DESCRIPTION:Choosing a repository is an important task that can impact the
  discoverability and long-term maintenance of your research data. There ar
 e several interactive tools designed to help with the selection process. T
 hese include filterable repository “finders\," which allow researchers t
 o identify and compare relevant repositories. In this session\, learners w
 ill learn when to use repository finders\, receive demonstrations of two r
 epository finders\, and participate in evaluating repositories based on th
 eir characteristics. Learners will receive a summary handout after attendi
 ng this session. This workshop is offered as part of UC Love Data Week. Ad
 vance registration required. Questions? Contact datalab-training@ucdavis.e
 du.
URL:https://events.library.ucdavis.edu/event/workshop-w2026-repository-fin
 ders
X-SOURCE:UC Davis Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Human x Machine: A Collaborative AI Learning Lab for Undergrads
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260210T180000Z
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260210T200000Z
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51817792488869
DESCRIPTION:Undergrads are invited to drop into our new AI Learning Lab se
 ssions! Participants will: Experiment safely with various AI tools (ChatGP
 T\, Claude\, Perplexity\, image generators\, research assistants\, etc.) i
 n a supportive environmentDevelop critical evaluation skills to assess AI 
 outputs for accuracy\, bias\, and appropriatenessLearn ethical frameworks 
 for integrating AI into academic work while maintaining integrityShare dis
 coveries and challenges with peers facing similar questions about AI useBu
 ild confidence in making informed decisions about when\, how\, and whether
  to use AI toolsUnderstand disciplinary differences in AI policies and bes
 t practices across fields Led by Student Services intern Rayan Mansoor\, t
 hese informal sessions will be held biweekly on Tuesdays through March 10 
 in Shields Library\, Learning Instruction Room\, Rm. 205. No prior experie
 nce with AI is necessary. Please bring your own device.
LOCATION:Shields Library\, Library Instruction Rm 205
URL:https://events.library.ucdavis.edu/event/human-x-machine-collaborative
 -ai-learning-lab
X-SOURCE:UC Davis Library
END:VEVENT
