BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Creative Writing Series: MaKshya Tolbert\, Poetry
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260212T003000Z
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260212T013000Z
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51533967807501
DESCRIPTION:Please join us for the next event in the 2025-2026 Creative Wr
 iting Series: a poetry reading and Q&A featuring poet MaKshya Tolbert! Thi
 s event is free and open to all\, and will be available in person and live
 streamed. MaKshya Tolbert practices poetry and placemaking in Virginia\, w
 here her grandmother raised her. She is the 2025 Art in Library Spaces Art
 ist-in-Residence at the University of Virginia\, and was the 2024 New City
  Arts Fellowship Guest Curator. Her recent poetry and prose can be found a
 t Poem-a-Day\, Emergence Magazine\, West Branch\, Poets for Science\, and 
 Ran Off With the Star Bassoon. Shade is a place is her first book. This ev
 ent is co-sponsored with the Department of African American and African St
 udies. The Creative Writing Series is presented by the UC Davis Department
  of English\, Creative Writing Master of Fine Arts Program\, and the UC Da
 vis Library. The views expressed in this series\, including descriptions a
 nd biographies\, are those of the speakers and not meant to represent the 
 views of any other person or institution.
LOCATION:Shields Library\, 205
URL:https://events.library.ucdavis.edu/event/creative-writing-series-maksh
 ya-tolbert-poetry
X-SOURCE:UC Davis Library
END:VEVENT
